This paper studies user behavior in congestion games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). It also uses real traffic data to validate its findings, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also uses mathematical proofs and analysis, which suggests it could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) or social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the cost of system optimum and Nash equilibrium, which could be considered under computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE).
